Best Kept Secret is an album of unreleased songs recorded
 by Leona Lewis before her time on The X-Factor. Simon Cowell 
was reportedly angered by the release of the album. It was released 
two weeks after her debut album Spirit, on 26 November 2007, through 
Juno Records, though all trace of the album was removed from Juno the
 same day
